article.headline: CS Bakersfield 66, Cal Poly-SLO 64
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Donavan Bragg sank a running jumper with two seconds left and Cal State Bakersfield edged Cal Poly 66-64 Tuesday. The shot capped a flurry of clutch plays on both sides in the final minute, including a 3-pointer by Cal Poly's Trae Clark that tied the game at 64-64. Trent Blakley led Bakersfield (4-9) with 17 points, while Alex Johnson and Bryan Emanuel added 10 points apiece. Titus Shelton had 18 points and nine rebounds for Cal Poly (3-6). Cal Poly led 32-29 at halftime in a half that featured nine lead changes and four ties. The teams remained close for the entire second half, and Bakersfield fell behind 61-59 after Shelton hit a short jumper with 53 seconds left. Half a minute later Emanuel answered with a 3, drew an offensive foul on Cal Poly's next possession, and Bragg hit two free throws to give Bakersfield a 64-61 lead.
